{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839016817,"sessionID":"ses_287bf31a7ffefWSUdz2WISoq65","part":{"id":"prt_d7840f1f1001ob8T5NzmTDZMyl","messageID":"msg_d7840e8eb0018HuhBS191Nj6SQ","sessionID":"ses_287bf31a7ffefWSUdz2WISoq65","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-cfa819067c5a4859aa43722b060312f4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube ŌĆö OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python Ōēź3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   ŌåÆ Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      Ōåö Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      ŌåÆ WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         Ōåö Redis/Valkey\n33:         ŌåÆ K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube ŌĆö OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python Ōēź3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775839016796,"end":1775839016816}}}}
